args:
Having discovered Prince Alfonse's location,
the party hurries to save him—but finds Chrom,
the prince of Ylisse, standing in their way.
He claims {player_name} will doom
the world to a bleak future, and challenges
the entire party to battle.
I was just out slaying fiends from the\nrifts with Elisanne and the others.
And while I was doing that, I spotted\nmy brother on the other side of a rift!
I think he was in another world—one\nbeyond the space between worlds.
You're saying an entrance to another world\nis open in the space BETWEEN worlds?!
I suspect its opening may have been\na reaction of sorts to Princess Sharena's\nability to control gateways.

I know I ain't the sharpest sandwich
on the platter, but what'n the hell is
going on again? Alfonse is off in
some other world?
Actually, I believe what I saw was not\nmy brother, but instead another world's \nVERSION of my brother.
However, that Alfonse was being held\ncaptive in a world that looked exactly\nlike the one we are in now.

I've heard of this. They say our world is
one of myriad alternate worlds, each of
which is but a different possibility for
how things might unfold.
Exactly. But it got me thinking: Maybe\nour Alfonse in THIS world is in the same\nlocation as the Alfonse in THAT world!
And where was Alfonse being held\nin this other world you saw?

The way Princess Sharena described it,
he's likely in ruins from the Second War
of Binding. I believe I should be able to
identify the exact location.
In that case, we should go take a look.\nAt this point, any small lead is more\nthan worth following up on.
I believe the spot is just ahead, but...
The vision I saw was near a sealed door,\nbut I'm not seeing one here.
A door... A dooooor... Hey, THAT'S a door!
Do you know this man, Sharena?\nIf he's another of your acquaintances—
Oh, I know him, all right! He's a good\nfriend and great hero from another world.

He's the prince of the Halidom of Ylisse,
and captain of the Shepherds who guard it.
He's also one of the vanished companions
that I mentioned earlier.
I'm so glad to see you safe, Chrom!
And I am supremely relieved to see\nyou safe as well, Princess Sharena.
It's been quite the whirlwind here, Chrom!\nLet me tell you all about—
I believe I have a solid grasp of it already.\nPrince Alfonse is held behind that door,\nand you've come to rescue him.
I'm afraid I can't let that happen.
I will not allow you to proceed.
Pray forgive me, but I fear it may be\nnecessary to fell you here and now,\nPrince {player_name}.
Why?! What have I done to you?!
A bleak future may be the end result of\nyour actions here, and I will not permit\nsuch a thing to come to pass.
I understand that you have a twin sister\nwho is currently being held captive\nof a sort.
Are you willing to cast aside everything\nin order to save her? Are you capable\nof sacrificing yourself, if necessary?
My sister Zethia means more to me\nthan anything, and I will do whatever\nis necessary to see her safe.
I will risk all to save her!
Then you are every inch the man\nI was told to expect.
But despite that—no, BECAUSE of it—\nthe future I fear may yet come to pass.
I must test you to determine whether you\nare worthy of deciding this world's fate,\nPrince {player_name}.

If you lack the strength, it will be you
who brings about this future of despair.
And if that is the case, then I fear you
will meet your end this day!
What is the meaning of this?!
I dunno what's going on here, fella,\nbut if ya wanna take down the boss,\nyer gonna have to go through me.
I would have expected nothing less.\nAnd while it pains me to say so,\nI cannot promise not to harm you.
All of you need to be careful—Chrom is\nthe finest swordsman in all of Ylisse!
Your warning is unnecessary, Princess.\nFrom the way he seeks to oppose us,\nhis strength could not be more clear.
But if he plans to stand in my way,\nI've no choice but to go through him.
I admire the steel in your eyes, Prince.\nAnd while I wish we did not have to cross\nswords like this, I, too, am unable to yield.
Now, let us each fight for what we must!
